      "date": "2024-02-19 19:17:23.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> Patch Set 1: Code-Review+1\n> \n> (2 comments)\n> \n> This makes me wonder if it is not possible to specify a different path for KFI at build time?  But I see \"with_o2ib\" is done the same way, and the old \"with_kfi\" also forced a specific path, so maybe that is just how the RPM build works...\n\nYes, --with <arg> just gets translated to a on/off. You can use --define \"kfipath <somepath>\" and I suppose we can setup for that eventuality, but at the moment it seems unlikely to be needed.",
